## 1. Purpose

Phase 3B is the inverse test of Phase 3A. Where 3A asks *"does (α−1) appear where predicted?"*, 3B asks *"does (α−1) refuse to appear where it isn't supposed to?"* The phase confirms classifier integrity on non-family surfaces and characterizes how V4's substrate handles fixtures that geometrically lack the algebraic branch structure (α−1) classifies.

This phase carries the heaviest classifier-integrity load in the (α−1) exhaustion campaign. Every `wrong_*_clean_emit` fired in Phase 3B is a direct hit on classifier integrity. Per `V4_AUDIT_FRAMEWORK.md`, "wrong" means V4-honest (uses `propagated_window_error`, not `standard_error`).

